					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953051#post-4476609</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12953051/scp-5566#post-4476609</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 22 Jan 2020 22:24:09 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>aismallard</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4598089</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Intern also proposed a &quot;kamikaze mission&quot; ending in an approved suicide to prevent infecting any others. Intern has been relocated to follow additional ethics course.</p> </blockquote> <p>I quite enjoyed this line.</p> <p>The piece overall though wasn't my favorite. Part of this could've been ameliorated with better formatting, seeing the logs over and over with little visual distinction made it harder to read. The tone wasn't as tight as I like it, and the pacing felt off. The snippets from other countries didn't seem related (like, why investigate in those places?), and the escalation didn't have me very hooked.</p> <p>Novote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
